additional_house_rules:
To be considerate to our neighbors, we kindly ask to keep things on the quieter-side after 10 pm.

Whilst we do a thorough professional clean between each guest stay, we kindly ask that you not eat or drink in bed. Prior to leaving, please clean and put away any dishes or kitchenware used and put any dirty towels in the hamper. It helps us get through our cleaning process quicker and allows us to keep cleaning costs down for you and future guests.

To ensure we keep the floorboards squeaky clean for our guests’ enjoyment, we have a no shoes policy inside our home. 

We understand that accidents happen. But we do ask that you please let us know when they do. Chances are we can fix them as effortlessly as possible which also means better chances of having your full security deposit returned too.

What you do in your personal time is entirely up to you, but when staying at our place we have a strict no drug use policy. This is just the law… not so much one of our rules.

To keep our costs down (and pass those savings on to our guests) we kindly ask that you switch off lights when not in use or leaving the house. Mother nature thanks you too.

We understand that for a whole variety of reasons, you may want additional guests to stay in the place. In the event that you want additional guests to stay, please contact us to let us know. We’re reasonable folk and will accommodate wherever possible.
description:
Gorgeous entire 2 BR apartment in Sugar Hill / Hamilton Heights! 20 minutes to midtown from nearby express and local trains (ABCD1). Great beds, huge comfy couch, beautiful kitchen, feng shui decor. This unique apartment on a quiet block uptown will be your peaceful escape during your trip to New York. 

Near a great grocery store and local favorites like Harlem Public, At The Wallace, The Handpulled Noodle, The Chipped Cup, Monkey Cup, Hamilton Bakery, Mama Sushi, and Anchor Wine Bar.

Both bedrooms have awesome mattresses, living room has a giant, super comfy couch and a fantastic entertainment setup, roku tv and speedy wifi, and the kitchen has gorgeous stainless appliances, dishwasher, and granite countertops.

Whole apt

Awesome coffee shops, bars, and restaurants like Harlem Public, At The Wallace, The Handpulled Noodle, Chipped Cup, Monkey Cup, Hamilton Bakery, Mama Sushi, Tsion Cafe, Anchor Wine Bar, and many more!

3 Blocks from the ABCD (145th St. stop) and 4 blocks from the 1 (145th st)

Please take your shoes off when inside the apartment! We will leave some space for you on our shoe rack at the door.
